What would you like to learn about ruby concurrency?

Concurrency updates in Ruby 2.0.  Support for Concurrency in JRuby.  Using some of the newer Java/Scala libraries for JRuby concurrency.

What do you wish ruby did better for concurrency?

Higher level primitives for concurrency so it's easier for library makers to support various types of concurrency, or having a standard way of describing concurrency requirements in gems.
